The paper deals with multiple attribute decision analysis (MADA) problems, which are often tackled using artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) techniques. The paper also discusses the evidential reasoning approach, which is a popular method in the field of AI and ML. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analysis and modification of algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also deals with uncertainty, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
